TASK_TITLE=Add doey-ctl nudge command — escape stuck panes and re-prompt
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_ASSIGNED_TO=W3
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Add a 'nudge' subcommand to doey-ctl that unsticks Claude instances. When a pane is stuck (post-hook hang, waiting for input, stalled compact), 'doey-ctl nudge <pane>' should: (1) Send Escape key to the pane, (2) Wait 1 second, (3) Send a re-prompt message ('Check your messages and resume.') via send-keys, (4) Update status to BUSY. Also support 'doey-ctl nudge --all' to cascade across all non-READY/non-RESERVED panes. This replaces manual tmux send-keys Escape + send-keys Enter patterns that Boss currently does by hand. Should be Go code in tui/cmd/doey-ctl/. The nudge command calls tmux send-keys under the hood.
